<text id="02-output-contract" title="Rails ActiveRecord Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the AR-discipline manifest this methodology produces. Validator enforces required keys + per-field constraints.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/ruby-activerecord.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["rails_version", "ruby_version", "query_objects", "uses_default_scope", "n_plus_one_gate_enabled"],
  "properties": {
    "rails_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^(7|8)\\."},
    "ruby_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^3\\."},
    "query_objects": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["class", "exposes_results_as_relation", "method_count"],
        "properties": {
          "class": {"type": "string", "pattern": "Query$"},
          "exposes_results_as_relation": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
          "method_count": {"type": "integer", "maximum": 10}
        }
      }
    },
    "uses_default_scope": {"type": "boolean", "const": false},
    "n_plus_one_gate_enabled": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
    "forbidden_patterns_found": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 0}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "rails_version": "7.1",
  "ruby_version": "3.3",
  "query_objects": [{"class": "Users::ActiveUsersQuery", "exposes_results_as_relation": true, "method_count": 6}],
  "uses_default_scope": false,
  "n_plus_one_gate_enabled": true,
  "forbidden_patterns_found": []
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "rails_version": "6.0",
  "ruby_version": "2.7",
  "query_objects": [{"class": "UserQueryGodObject", "exposes_results_as_relation": false, "method_count": 32}],
  "uses_default_scope": true,
  "n_plus_one_gate_enabled": false,
  "forbidden_patterns_found": ["default_scope on User"]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Rails/Ruby too old; query object returns array + 32 methods; default_scope on; no N+1 gate.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>`default_scope { ... }` on any model.</item>
      <item>Query Object `results` returning an array (`.to_a`) instead of a relation.</item>
      <item>`Model.all.each` on growable tables.</item>
      <item>String-interpolated `where("col = '#{input}'")`.</item>
      <item>Query Object with &gt; 10 chainable methods (split it).</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-ruby-activerecord.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
